definitions.definition: The energy and strength for continuing to do something over a long period of time; power of sustained exertion, or resistance to hardship, illness etc.
examples: He has a lot of stamina . I suppose that's why he can run for a long time.

definitions.definition: ( obsolete , uncountable , plural only ) The basic elements of a thing; rudimentary structures or qualities.
